cs.RO, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of a multi-robot system for material classification and mapping in unknown environments.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper uses audio signals produced by tapping different materials to classify them.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper uses machine learning techniques (SVM) to classify the materials based on the audio signals.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses a machine learning algorithm (SVM) to classify the materials.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses Velodyne LiDAR to assist in the exploration of the unknown environment.
